The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, July 17, 2004 				 Telecom gear makers dial broadband code
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, July 16: The Telecom Equipment Manufacturers Association (Tema) has formed India Broadband Forum (IBF) to push the broadband revolution. The IBF is targeting 3 million broadband users by 2006, 10 million by 2008 and 20 million by 2010. The different technology options to realise these objectives are available in India.Tema president N. K. Goyal, who is also the first president of IBF, said, Broadband will soon take its due place, which is the centrestage of the digital world in India. The rewards for those who can harness this platform will be huge. The real winners will be those who align themselves with the right partners and can present the best possible choices in terms of technology, solutions and service.																								IBF will be headed by an advisory body consisting of six professionals from the information, communications and telecom segments. The forum hopes to provide technical, strategic and marketing support to various entities involved in the broadband segment with a view to promote, deliver and sustain profitable broadband products, service and business in India. 
